those normal sacrifices, and are here adopted.

<span id="fn_495"></span>[197:3](sbe01201.htm#fr_497.md) Cf. Ait. Âr. I, 2,
1, 2.

<span id="fn_496"></span>[197:4](sbe01201.htm#fr_498.md) Nothing higher
than the great can be wished for or obtained. Comm.

<span id="fn_497"></span>[198:1](sbe01201.htm#fr_499.md) All who perform
the ceremony obtain Brahman. Cf. § 12.

<span id="fn_498"></span>[198:2](sbe01201.htm#fr_500.md) The third wheel,
in addition to the usual two wheels, forms the end of a carriage, as
before the dhuh, Cf. I, 5, 2, 14. This day also is the end.

<span id="fn_499"></span>[198:3](sbe01201.htm#fr_501.md) Consisting of
Vedic hymns and dances, &c. Comm.

<span id="fn_500"></span>[199:1](sbe01201.htm#fr_502.md) Cf. § 4.

<span id="fn_501"></span>[199:2](sbe01201.htm#fr_503.md) Cf. I, 5, 2, 8.

